hear this possibly.

00:21:39.680 --> 00:21:42.960 align:middle line:84%
Because it touches something
very deep and very real

00:21:42.960 --> 00:21:44.000 align:middle line:90%
within each of us.

00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:46.820 align:middle line:84%
I think we all know that
we're here for a reason.

00:21:46.820 --> 00:21:49.220 align:middle line:84%
We all know that there's
something much, much bigger

00:21:49.220 --> 00:21:51.540 align:middle line:84%
happening then what
we've come to understand

00:21:51.540 --> 00:21:53.510 align:middle line:84%
and what we've been
led to believe.

00:21:53.510 --> 00:21:56.690 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sharing the possibilities
that the evidence suggests.

00:21:56.690 --> 00:22:00.140 align:middle line:84%
The possibility of
running out of space

00:22:00.140 --> 00:22:03.290 align:middle line:84%
in our simulation that was
only one possibility of what

00:22:03.290 --> 00:22:05.580 align:middle line:90%
could end this experience.

00:22:05.580 --> 00:22:09.620 align:middle line:84%
The second is an unexpected
event, a tremendous release

00:22:09.620 --> 00:22:11.680 align:middle line:90%
of energy of some kind.

00:22:11.680 --> 00:22:15.530 align:middle line:84%
And that thinking
coincides with the theme

00:22:15.530 --> 00:22:18.590 align:middle line:84%
of what our simulation is
all about to begin with.

00:22:18.590 --> 00:22:23.870 align:middle line:84%
The theme of life on Earth
for the last 5,000 years

00:22:23.870 --> 00:22:27.530 align:middle line:84%
has been primarily a
theme of war and conflict.

00:22:27.530 --> 00:22:32.180 align:middle line:84%
For over 5,000 years, humans
have almost continuously been

00:22:32.180 --> 00:22:36.380 align:middle line:84%
in conflict to one degree or
another in one form or another.

00:22:36.380 --> 00:22:39.670 align:middle line:84%
And the consistency
of that experience

00:22:39.670 --> 00:22:44.130 align:middle line:84%
suggests that it must play a
powerful role in our simulation

00:22:44.130 --> 00:22:47.440 align:middle line:84%
and why we're here
to begin with.

00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:50.990 align:middle line:84%
Now the archaeological record
preserves that history.

00:22:50.990 --> 00:22:54.450 align:middle line:84%
And it tells us of different
kinds of global conflict.

00:22:54.450 --> 00:22:57.170 align:middle line:84%
And for me, this is the
value of looking at the past.

00:22:57.170 --> 00:22:58.810 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, sure it's interesting.

00:22:58.810 --> 00:23:02.030 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's interesting to
look at ancient civilizations.

00:23:02.030 --> 00:23:04.850 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting to see what
people have done in the past.

00:23:04.850 --> 00:23:09.290 align:middle line:84%
For me as a scientist, the
value of looking into the past

00:23:09.290 --> 00:23:14.390 align:middle line:84%
is to recognize the patterns,
the trends, and the cycles

00:23:14.390 --> 00:23:16.670 align:middle line:84%
of those who have
come before us;

00:23:16.670 --> 00:23:20.340 align:middle line:84%
and to compare those to where
we are today and ask ourselves,

00:23:20.340 --> 00:23:22.700 align:middle line:90%
are we repeating those trends?

00:23:22.700 --> 00:23:24.320 align:middle line:90%
Are we repeating the patterns?

00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:26.030 align:middle line:90%
Are we repeating the cycles?

00:23:26.030 --> 00:23:28.740 align:middle line:84%
And it would make sense
if the answer is yes.

00:23:28.740 --> 00:23:31.670 align:middle line:84%
Now that we understand
the fractal code

00:23:31.670 --> 00:23:33.560 align:middle line:90%
and Newton's laws of energy.

00:23:33.560 --> 00:23:35.930 align:middle line:84%
Because the fractal
code says that we

00:23:35.930 --> 00:23:39.560 align:middle line:84%
will continue those patterns
until something-- something

00:23:39.560 --> 00:23:41.060 align:middle line:90%
in the variable changes.

00:23:41.060 --> 00:23:43.190 align:middle line:10%
And Newton's law
tells us that once

00:23:43.190 --> 00:23:46.190 align:middle line:10%
the energy is set into
motion that same energy is

00:23:46.190 --> 00:23:49.440 align:middle line:10%
going to continue until
something changes the energy.

00:23:49.440 --> 00:23:52.210 align:middle line:84%
So if there is a
thinking of conflict,

00:23:52.210 --> 00:23:57.150 align:middle line:84%
if there is a fear that there's
not enough, of scarcity,

00:23:57.150 --> 00:24:00.830 align:middle line:84%
if there is a fear of
the unknown, a fear

00:24:00.830 --> 00:24:03.920 align:middle line:84%
of other people, a fear of
what those people's lives mean

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:07.430 align:middle line:84%
to us; and if that fear is
so ancient and so primal

00:24:07.430 --> 00:24:10.640 align:middle line:84%
that it is played out in every
civilization for the last 5,000

00:24:10.640 --> 00:24:13.340 align:middle line:84%
years and beyond,
then it makes sense

00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:15.590 align:middle line:84%
that this idea of
conflict and war

00:24:15.590 --> 00:24:19.920 align:middle line:84%
would be a primary reason for
us to be in this simulation.

00:24:19.920 --> 00:24:21.590 align:middle line:84%
And the archeology
supports this.

00:24:21.590 --> 00:24:25.610 align:middle line:84%
If Bostrom's mathematic
arguments are correct,

00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:29.690 align:middle line:84%
the fact that we're here today
asking these questions that's

00:24:29.690 --> 00:24:31.070 align:middle line:90%
good news.

00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:34.340 align:middle line:84%
Because it implies that we
have the wisdom to recognize

00:24:34.340 --> 00:24:36.950 align:middle line:84%
we're at a point where we
need to ask these questions.

00:24:36.950 --> 00:24:41.130 align:middle line:84%
It tells us there is a
need for this simulation.

00:24:41.130 --> 00:24:42.710 align:middle line:90%
So these are big ideas.

00:24:42.710 --> 00:24:43.910 align:middle line:90%
And I know they are.

00:24:43.910 --> 00:24:46.430 align:middle line:84%
And I'm bringing
them together now

00:24:46.430 --> 00:24:49.640 align:middle line:84%
at the close of this series,
because we have the vocabulary.

00:24:49.640 --> 00:24:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And we have a new context within
which to share these ideas.

00:24:53.610 --> 00:24:56.150 align:middle line:84%
So, what I'd like to do now
is give you a specific example

00:24:56.150 --> 00:24:59.660 align:middle line:84%
of what I'm talking about, this
pattern of conflict and whether

00:24:59.660 --> 00:25:01.020 align:middle line:90%
or not repeating the cycle.

00:25:01.020 --> 00:25:04.160 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to use archeology,
contemporary archeology to do

00:25:04.160 --> 00:25:05.760 align:middle line:90%
this.

00:25:05.760 --> 00:25:07.400 align:middle line:84%
There was an
archaeological discovery

00:25:07.400 --> 00:25:11.450 align:middle line:84%
that was made mid-20th century,
a very mysterious, very

00:25:11.450 --> 00:25:12.410 align:middle line:90%
powerful discovery.

00:25:12.410 --> 00:25:14.440 align:middle line:90%
It's very controversial today.

00:25:14.440 --> 00:25:18.080 align:middle line:84%
And it is in the region
that is now called Pakistan.

00:25:18.080 --> 00:25:21.650 align:middle line:84%
It used to be India before
that the division happened,

00:25:21.650 --> 00:25:24.920 align:middle line:84%
and in the disputed areas
between India and Pakistan

00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:26.890 align:middle line:90%
in the Kashmir area.

00:25:26.890 --> 00:25:30.970 align:middle line:84%
There is evidence of an
advanced technological society

00:25:30.970 --> 00:25:33.660 align:middle line:84%
and advanced technological
civilization.

00:25:33.660 --> 00:25:35.575 align:middle line:84%
They had hot and
cold running water.

00:25:35.575 --> 00:25:37.160 align:middle line:90%
They had flush toilets.

00:25:37.160 --> 00:25:38.930 align:middle line:90%
They had stained glass windows.

00:25:38.930 --> 00:25:40.310 align:middle line:90%
They had advanced mathematics.

00:25:40.310 --> 00:25:43.310 align:middle line:84%
They had beautiful,
beautiful art.

00:25:43.310 --> 00:25:47.750 align:middle line:84%
And this advanced civilization
came to an abrupt end.

00:25:47.750 --> 00:25:51.020 align:middle line:84%
And we know that because
of what was left behind.

00:25:51.020 --> 00:25:54.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, when the
scientists began finding

00:25:54.260 --> 00:25:56.690 align:middle line:84%
this evidence of
this civilization,

00:25:56.690 --> 00:25:59.270 align:middle line:84%
one of the first
things that they found

00:25:59.270 --> 00:26:04.190 align:middle line:84%
were walls and floors that were
made of natural stone, granite,

00:26:04.190 --> 00:26:05.940 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:09.904 align:middle line:84%
But the term that was used
that the stones were vitrified.

00:26:09.904 --> 00:26:10.820 align:middle line:90%
Now, what this means--

00:26:10.820 --> 00:26:13.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to use granite
as an example-- granite

00:26:13.190 --> 00:26:17.060 align:middle line:84%
is made of three
minerals-- quartz, feldspar

00:26:17.060 --> 00:26:19.790 align:middle line:90%
which is a clay, and mica.

00:26:19.790 --> 00:26:23.460 align:middle line:84%
So, the quartz, the feldspar,
in the mica were in place.

00:26:23.460 --> 00:26:29.040 align:middle line:84%
However, the quartz in place
was melted within the stone.

00:26:29.040 --> 00:26:32.660 align:middle line:84%
Now, to melt the courts
in place requires

00:26:32.660 --> 00:26:35.870 align:middle line:84%
number one, a high amount
of heat to do the melting;

00:26:35.870 --> 00:26:39.050 align:middle line:84%
but number two, it
has to be very fast.

00:26:39.050 --> 00:26:42.020 align:middle line:84%
Because it didn't destroy
the floors and the walls.

00:26:42.020 --> 00:26:46.880 align:middle line:84%
So, it suggest a
rapid very high heat,

00:26:46.880 --> 00:26:49.490 align:middle line:84%
some point in our ancient
past that melted the quartz,

00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:50.940 align:middle line:90%
left everything in place.

00:26:50.940 --> 00:26:54.790 align:middle line:84%
They also found
mysterious little spheres,

00:26:54.790 --> 00:26:56.830 align:middle line:90%
little balls of clay.

00:26:56.830 --> 00:26:58.550 align:middle line:84%
They didn't know
what these were.

00:26:58.550 --> 00:27:00.200 align:middle line:84%
And when they
began to understand

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:02.750 align:middle line:84%
that the walls and the
floors were vitrified

00:27:02.750 --> 00:27:06.740 align:middle line:84%
from a rapid intense heat, they
found that these little spheres

00:27:06.740 --> 00:27:11.600 align:middle line:84%
were clay vases that had
also been exposed to the heat

00:27:11.600 --> 00:27:14.630 align:middle line:90%
and were simply melted in place.

00:27:14.630 --> 00:27:16.960 align:middle line:84%
So, the scientists
are asking, what

00:27:16.960 --> 00:27:19.370 align:middle line:84%
is it that could
have possibly caused

00:27:19.370 --> 00:27:23.180 align:middle line:84%
this kind of intense
heat, intense enough

00:27:23.180 --> 00:27:26.690 align:middle line:84%
to melt the quartz, but so
fast that the walls were still

00:27:26.690 --> 00:27:28.190 align:middle line:90%
in place?

00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:29.960 align:middle line:84%
Well, some of the
human skeletons

00:27:29.960 --> 00:27:32.840 align:middle line:84%
that were discovered-- and
this is very controversial.

00:27:32.840 --> 00:27:36.410 align:middle line:84%
Some of the human skeletons
may give us a clue.

00:27:36.410 --> 00:27:41.360 align:middle line:84%
The skeletons were found
primarily in this location.

00:27:41.360 --> 00:27:46.190 align:middle line:84%
They were all at one end of
this ancient city in what

00:27:46.190 --> 00:27:48.440 align:middle line:90%
are called postures of flight.

00:27:48.440 --> 00:27:51.230 align:middle line:84%
And these are Russian
scientists in the mid-1960s

00:27:51.230 --> 00:27:55.340 align:middle line:84%
that were the first to find
this, postures of flight.

00:27:55.340 --> 00:27:56.580 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:27:56.580 --> 00:27:58.790 align:middle line:84%
It means they were running
away from something.

00:27:58.790 --> 00:28:04.380 align:middle line:84%
They were all at one end of
the city and they were running.

00:28:04.380 --> 00:28:07.490 align:middle line:10%
And the giveaway is that
some of the skeletons

00:28:07.490 --> 00:28:09.180 align:middle line:10%
were actually radioactive.

00:28:09.180 --> 00:28:10.850 align:middle line:84%
They were more
radioactive than you

00:28:10.850 --> 00:28:14.780 align:middle line:84%
would expect from the
normal background radiation

00:28:14.780 --> 00:28:17.940 align:middle line:84%
that we have from the
earth and from cosmic rays.

00:28:17.940 --> 00:28:19.850 align:middle line:90%
We're all absorbing radiation.

00:28:19.850 --> 00:28:22.370 align:middle line:84%
But the level in these
skeletons was higher

00:28:22.370 --> 00:28:24.105 align:middle line:90%
than it should have been.

00:28:24.105 --> 00:28:25.730 align:middle line:84%
So, the scientists
are looking at this.

00:28:25.730 --> 00:28:26.970 align:middle line:84%
They're putting
this all together

00:28:26.970 --> 00:28:29.095 align:middle line:84%
and they're saying, what
in the world could happen.

00:28:29.095 --> 00:28:30.920 align:middle line:84%
And this is one of
those places where

00:28:30.920 --> 00:28:33.950 align:middle line:84%
if you look at the
evidence itself,

00:28:33.950 --> 00:28:36.720 align:middle line:84%
you're never going
to solve the mystery.

00:28:36.720 --> 00:28:38.540 align:middle line:90%
We don't live in a vacuum.

00:28:38.540 --> 00:28:40.550 align:middle line:84%
History does not
occur in a vacuum.

00:28:40.550 --> 00:28:43.740 align:middle line:84%
And this is where
context is so important.

00:28:43.740 --> 00:28:45.670 align:middle line:84%
So, the evidence is
showing us a mystery.

00:28:45.670 --> 00:28:48.600 align:middle line:10%
However in that
part of the world,

00:28:48.600 --> 00:28:51.650 align:middle line:10%
the sacred text of
Mahabharata tells

00:28:51.650 --> 00:28:55.424 align:middle line:10%
a story that is believed
to have been a fairytale.

00:28:55.424 --> 00:28:57.590 align:middle line:84%
It is believed to have been
a fairytale because what

00:28:57.590 --> 00:29:01.460 align:middle line:84%
it describes is something
that is unfathomable up

00:29:01.460 --> 00:29:03.170 align:middle line:90%
until the 20th century.

00:29:03.170 --> 00:29:06.290 align:middle line:84%
What this text
describes makes no sense

00:29:06.290 --> 00:29:09.536 align:middle line:84%
until the technology of
the mid-20th century.

00:29:09.536 --> 00:29:10.910 align:middle line:84%
So, what I'd like
to do, I'd like

00:29:10.910 --> 00:29:13.670 align:middle line:84%
to read a portion of
an English translation

00:29:13.670 --> 00:29:15.980 align:middle line:90%
to you from this text.

00:29:15.980 --> 00:29:18.170 align:middle line:84%
And then let's take
this translation,

00:29:18.170 --> 00:29:20.360 align:middle line:84%
apply it to what has been
found archaeologically,

00:29:20.360 --> 00:29:22.610 align:middle line:84%
and see where that
leaves us in terms

00:29:22.610 --> 00:29:25.250 align:middle line:90%
of the cycles in our simulation.

00:29:25.250 --> 00:29:27.600 align:middle line:84%
So here are passages
from the text.

00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:32.150 align:middle line:84%
There were two armies
that were in a great war

00:29:32.150 --> 00:29:34.020 align:middle line:90%
at the end of a cycle.

00:29:34.020 --> 00:29:34.970 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:29:34.970 --> 00:29:36.630 align:middle line:90%
The two armies were fighting.

00:29:36.630 --> 00:29:38.570 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
armies began to lose

00:29:38.570 --> 00:29:40.580 align:middle line:84%
and they resorted
to a weapon that

00:29:40.580 --> 00:29:42.320 align:middle line:90%
had never been used before.

00:29:42.320 --> 00:29:44.960 align:middle line:84%
And this is the way the
text describes the weapon.

00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:47.810 align:middle line:84%
It says "a single
projectile charged

00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:50.090 align:middle line:84%
with all the power
of the universe,

00:29:50.090 --> 00:29:53.780 align:middle line:84%
an incandescent column of
smoke and flame, as bright

00:29:53.780 --> 00:29:57.890 align:middle line:84%
as a thousand suns rose
in all of its splendor.

00:29:57.890 --> 00:30:02.360 align:middle line:84%
A perpendicular explosion with
the billowing smoke clouds.

00:30:02.360 --> 00:30:05.960 align:middle line:10%
The cloud of smoke rising
after the first explosion,

00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:09.140 align:middle line:10%
formed into expanding
circles like the opening

00:30:09.140 --> 00:30:10.010 align:middle line:10%
of a giant parasol."

00:30:10.010 --> 00:30:13.260 align:middle line:90%


00:30:13.260 --> 00:30:16.260 align:middle line:84%
"It was an unknown weapon,
an iron thunderbolt,

00:30:16.260 --> 00:30:18.890 align:middle line:84%
a gigantic messenger
of death which

00:30:18.890 --> 00:30:23.250 align:middle line:84%
reduced to ashes the entire race
of Vrishnis and the Andhakas.

00:30:23.250 --> 00:30:27.130 align:middle line:84%
The corpses were so burned
as to be unrecognizable.

00:30:27.130 --> 00:30:28.830 align:middle line:90%
The hair and the nails fell out.

00:30:28.830 --> 00:30:31.360 align:middle line:84%
Pottery broke without
apparent cause,

00:30:31.360 --> 00:30:33.600 align:middle line:90%
and the birds turned white.

00:30:33.600 --> 00:30:36.570 align:middle line:84%
After a few hours all
food stuffs were infected,

00:30:36.570 --> 00:30:38.790 align:middle line:84%
and to escape from
this fire, the soldiers

00:30:38.790 --> 00:30:40.710 align:middle line:84%
threw themselves
into the streams

00:30:40.710 --> 00:30:42.985 align:middle line:84%
to wash themselves
and their equipment."

00:30:42.985 --> 00:30:45.660 align:middle line:90%


00:30:45.660 --> 00:30:47.790 align:middle line:84%
So, the description
that you've just heard

00:30:47.790 --> 00:30:49.470 align:middle line:90%
is from an ancient text.

00:30:49.470 --> 00:30:53.130 align:middle line:84%
However what it
describes sounds very

00:30:53.130 --> 00:30:57.120 align:middle line:84%
much like a contemporary
description of the unthinkable,

00:30:57.120 --> 00:31:01.830 align:middle line:84%
of a nuclear explosion happening
some time in our ancient past.

00:31:01.830 --> 00:31:03.330 align:middle line:90%
Is it possible?

00:31:03.330 --> 00:31:06.510 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible that these
advanced civilizations

00:31:06.510 --> 00:31:09.480 align:middle line:84%
that we now know are cyclic
that have risen and fallen

00:31:09.480 --> 00:31:12.090 align:middle line:84%
in the past, that
had electricity, that

00:31:12.090 --> 00:31:14.430 align:middle line:84%
had hot and cold running
water, and flush toilets,

00:31:14.430 --> 00:31:16.500 align:middle line:84%
and stained glass
windows, and advanced

00:31:16.500 --> 00:31:21.570 align:middle line:84%
mathematics of the cosmos and
of nature itself; is it possible

00:31:21.570 --> 00:31:25.470 align:middle line:84%
that they began a path
that we are following now?

00:31:25.470 --> 00:31:28.170 align:middle line:84%
Are we the first atomic
civilization or has there

00:31:28.170 --> 00:31:30.090 align:middle line:90%
been one before us?

00:31:30.090 --> 00:31:33.000 align:middle line:10%
Well, the father of the
modern nuclear program,

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:36.390 align:middle line:10%
Robert Oppenheimer, was
asked this very question.

00:31:36.390 --> 00:31:39.960 align:middle line:10%
In an interview that he was
doing at Rochester University

00:31:39.960 --> 00:31:41.670 align:middle line:10%
there was a student
that asked it,

00:31:41.670 --> 00:31:43.890 align:middle line:10%
and he said, Dr.
Oppenheimer, how

00:31:43.890 --> 00:31:46.290 align:middle line:84%
do you feel after
having exploded

00:31:46.290 --> 00:31:49.200 align:middle line:90%
the first atomic bomb on Earth?

00:31:49.200 --> 00:31:50.820 align:middle line:90%
And Oppenheimer replied.

00:31:50.820 --> 00:31:53.280 align:middle line:84%
And his reply
shocked the audience.

00:31:53.280 --> 00:31:56.400 align:middle line:84%
It shocked the person who
was asking a question.

00:31:56.400 --> 00:31:58.920 align:middle line:84%
Because Oppenheimer
said, well, he

00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:04.830 align:middle line:84%
said not the first atomic bomb,
but the first in modern times.

00:32:04.830 --> 00:32:08.010 align:middle line:84%
Robert Oppenheimer was a
student of the Mahabharata.

00:32:08.010 --> 00:32:11.820 align:middle line:84%
He was a student of the
Bhagavad Gita, the related text.

00:32:11.820 --> 00:32:15.370 align:middle line:84%
And he firmly believed
that we are, in fact,

00:32:15.370 --> 00:32:18.090 align:middle line:84%
a cyclic civilization
and that we are repeating

00:32:18.090 --> 00:32:20.220 align:middle line:90%
a pattern from the past.

00:32:20.220 --> 00:32:23.820 align:middle line:84%
And if we are within the
context of our simulation,

00:32:23.820 --> 00:32:28.770 align:middle line:84%
we have to ask, what are the
consequences of our simulation

00:32:28.770 --> 00:32:33.170 align:middle line:84%
if we were to engage in a
large-scale nuclear war?

00:32:33.170 --> 00:32:37.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, think about this in terms
of this entire conversation.

00:32:37.050 --> 00:32:40.650 align:middle line:84%
The release of energy
from a nuclear weapon

00:32:40.650 --> 00:32:44.790 align:middle line:84%
is information, tremendous
amounts of information.

00:32:44.790 --> 00:32:48.540 align:middle line:84%
How much information would
be released into the system

00:32:48.540 --> 00:32:53.310 align:middle line:84%
if we had multiple nuclear
explosions in a conflict,

00:32:53.310 --> 00:32:57.030 align:middle line:84%
like we've had perhaps in
the past on a limited scale?

00:32:57.030 --> 00:32:59.364 align:middle line:84%
How long could we
continue to produce

00:32:59.364 --> 00:33:00.780 align:middle line:84%
that kind of
information before we

00:33:00.780 --> 00:33:04.860 align:middle line:84%
reach that capacity, that limit
that we talked about earlier?

00:33:04.860 --> 00:33:07.320 align:middle line:84%
So, this whole idea
of the simulation

00:33:07.320 --> 00:33:11.310 align:middle line:84%
is giving us new ways to think
about us, about what we're

00:33:11.310 --> 00:33:13.190 align:middle line:84%
living, about what's
happening in our world

00:33:13.190 --> 00:33:15.210 align:middle line:84%
and what's happening
in our lives.

00:33:15.210 --> 00:33:17.700 align:middle line:84%
If the unthinkable has
happened in the past,

00:33:17.700 --> 00:33:20.160 align:middle line:84%
are we repeating that
cycle again in our lives?

00:33:20.160 --> 00:33:21.810 align:middle line:84%
And if we are, can
we recognize it?

00:33:21.810 --> 00:33:24.780 align:middle line:84%
Do we have the wisdom
to recognize it

00:33:24.780 --> 00:33:28.230 align:middle line:84%
and as Newton's law
says, shift the energy.

00:33:28.230 --> 00:33:29.700 align:middle line:90%
Move to a new course.

00:33:29.700 --> 00:33:32.580 align:middle line:84%
Plug in a new variable
into that fractal code,

00:33:32.580 --> 00:33:35.280 align:middle line:84%
so that we can
avoid the suffering

00:33:35.280 --> 00:33:38.910 align:middle line:84%
that obviously would
come from such a path.

00:33:38.910 --> 00:33:40.897 align:middle line:84%
The common thread that
runs through every one

00:33:40.897 --> 00:33:42.605 align:middle line:84%
of the possibilities
that I've described,

00:33:42.605 --> 00:33:44.396 align:middle line:84%
whether we're talking
about climate change,

00:33:44.396 --> 00:33:48.060 align:middle line:84%
or we're talking about
disease pandemics or war;

00:33:48.060 --> 00:33:51.900 align:middle line:84%
is that every one of
these possibilities

00:33:51.900 --> 00:33:54.150 align:middle line:90%
is related to human choice.

00:33:54.150 --> 00:33:58.020 align:middle line:84%
It's the choices that we
are making within our lives,

00:33:58.020 --> 00:34:01.680 align:middle line:84%
now within our simulation,
that are resulting

00:34:01.680 --> 00:34:05.340 align:middle line:84%
in the very conditions that
could end this experience based

00:34:05.340 --> 00:34:07.080 align:middle line:90%
upon the way we think.

00:34:07.080 --> 00:34:09.255 align:middle line:84%
Now, my sense,
personally; my sense

00:34:09.255 --> 00:34:13.530 align:middle line:84%
is because conflict has
played such a dominant role

00:34:13.530 --> 00:34:16.920 align:middle line:84%
throughout history and that
that theme is playing out today

00:34:16.920 --> 00:34:21.989 align:middle line:84%
and it appears to be coming to a
head, again and again this idea

00:34:21.989 --> 00:34:23.250 align:middle line:90%
keeps coming up.

00:34:23.250 --> 00:34:25.679 align:middle line:84%
My sense is that we are
learning to create a world where

00:34:25.679 --> 00:34:29.040 align:middle line:84%
war doesn't exist or
it's become obsolete.

00:34:29.040 --> 00:34:31.860 align:middle line:84%
And we're doing so by
developing the potential that

00:34:31.860 --> 00:34:33.989 align:middle line:84%
lives within each of
us as individuals.

00:34:33.989 --> 00:34:38.040 align:middle line:84%
And remember, the better we know
ourselves, the less we fear--

00:34:38.040 --> 00:34:43.960 align:middle line:84%
the less we fear one another and
the less we fear the unknown.

00:34:43.960 --> 00:34:45.449 align:middle line:84%
If we're honest
with ourselves, we

00:34:45.449 --> 00:34:47.314 align:middle line:90%
know that the world is changing.

00:34:47.314 --> 00:34:49.230 align:middle line:84%
And we also know that
the old ways of thinking

00:34:49.230 --> 00:34:52.080 align:middle line:84%
are failing when it comes
to solving the big problems

00:34:52.080 --> 00:34:54.449 align:middle line:90%
like climate change and war.

00:34:54.449 --> 00:34:57.660 align:middle line:84%
We need a new way to think about
our world and a new language

00:34:57.660 --> 00:34:59.460 align:middle line:90%
to solve our problems.

00:34:59.460 --> 00:35:02.220 align:middle line:84%
Simulation by design
is an invitation.

00:35:02.220 --> 00:35:04.980 align:middle line:84%
It invites us to think
differently about ourselves,

00:35:04.980 --> 00:35:07.530 align:middle line:84%
